[Amit Varma]: with this guy is like, my credo like, you know, when Shruti Rajgopalan, our friend asked me about,

02:28:36.760 --> 02:28:40.360
[Amit Varma]: you know, she was starting her podcast ideas of India back in the day. And she had long

02:28:40.360 --> 02:28:43.400
[Amit Varma]: conversations with me about what it should be like and all of that. And I gave her much of

02:28:43.400 --> 02:28:48.760
[Amit Varma]: this advice. But one of the things I said, was that when I conceived of the scene in the unseen,

02:28:48.760 --> 02:28:53.000
[Amit Varma]: I conceived of it as not just reaching across space in terms of geography, people listen to

02:28:53.000 --> 02:28:59.000
[Amit Varma]: me from everywhere, but reaching across time. So if you listen to it in 2030, it is still valuable

02:28:59.000 --> 02:29:03.640
[Amit Varma]: to you. So my advice to her was that when you're thinking about the kind of content you want to do,

02:29:03.640 --> 02:29:08.680
[Amit Varma]: don't think about what someone listening to episode one is going to hear. Think about what

02:29:08.680 --> 02:29:15.560
[Amit Varma]: somebody discovering you at episode 100 will binge on. Right. And when you think about it like that,

02:29:15.560 --> 02:29:21.720
[Amit Varma]: that changes everything. Right. And speaking of the long term, I think now it's, you know,

02:29:21.720 --> 02:29:26.680
[Amit Varma]: a lot of your book, Money Wise, Timeless Lessons on Building Wealth, which I enjoyed reading so

02:29:26.680 --> 02:29:31.800
[Amit Varma]: much. And I sometimes I worry if I'm too old to benefit from the advice. So you have, you know,

02:29:31.800 --> 02:29:36.280
[Amit Varma]: a section addressing just that, and you say I'm not so you know, and that takes a long term view

02:29:36.280 --> 02:29:40.040
[Amit Varma]: as well. And you know, let's take a quick commercial break. And when we come back,

