[Guest]: if they're smart enough.

03:39:31.640 --> 03:39:36.120
[Amit Varma]: Was it Keynes who said that the markets can stay irrational longer than you can stay solvent?

03:39:36.120 --> 03:39:41.560
[Amit Varma]: So if you're betting on, you know, markets crashing, yeah, sure, they will. But when?

03:39:41.560 --> 03:39:47.400
[Guest]: Yeah, Alan Greenspan, and I keep using this example, so I'm sorry if I've used this before.

03:39:47.960 --> 03:39:52.600
[Guest]: He said in 1996, December, that the markets were irrationally exuberant.

03:39:52.600 --> 03:39:57.000
[Guest]: Now, this is the most famous central banker of our time, the guy who's presided over the

03:39:57.000 --> 03:40:01.960
[Guest]: largest amount of easier money policies, and therefore, the largest amount of stock market

03:40:01.960 --> 03:40:07.800
[Guest]: excesses. He's telling you the markets exuberant in December 1996, the market proceeds to go up

03:40:07.800 --> 03:40:15.000
[Guest]: another 50% from there, crashes 30%. At the time it crashed the lowest point of which it took two

03:40:15.000 --> 03:40:19.960
[Guest]: and a half years to crash. And when it did, the lowest point of the crash was still above the

03:40:19.960 --> 03:40:24.600
[Guest]: point at which he had said the markets were irrationally exuberant. So he was right, but he

03:40:24.600 --> 03:40:32.040
[Guest]: was wrong. And this is the most celebrated central banker of all time. So I'm like, if he couldn't

03:40:32.040 --> 03:40:38.040
[Guest]: get it, what are the chances anyone else can with the data information we have at hand, we can be,

03:40:38.040 --> 03:40:43.560
[Guest]: you can be the so Dave Barry writes about this in his book, he talks about Florida and old people.

03:40:43.560 --> 03:40:48.200
[Guest]: And he says, there is a there are people who put their left indicator on as soon as they get out

03:40:48.200 --> 03:40:54.760
[Guest]: of their house, and it stays on for like forever. So he says that it's called an eventual left.

03:40:54.760 --> 03:40:59.160
[Guest]: So at some point in life, this guy's going to take a left turn. And you just don't know when.

03:40:59.160 --> 03:41:02.840
[Guest]: So when you drive behind such a person, you have to know that this is an eventual left kind of

03:41:02.840 --> 03:41:09.960
[Guest]: driver. This is the point about naysayers in the market, they will eventually be right. But,

03:41:10.520 --> 03:41:15.640
[Amit Varma]: you know, when is the question. So, you know, like this, that old saying that,

03:41:15.640 --> 03:41:20.440
[Amit Varma]: you know, so and so who predicted the last three recessions predicted a total of 15 recessions,

03:41:20.440 --> 03:41:24.520
[Amit Varma]: right? And I guess the same could be said for stock market crashes. Your lesson number three

03:41:24.520 --> 03:41:29.160
[Amit Varma]: is very interesting. And you demonstrate this in such detail that I have to just ask people to go

03:41:29.160 --> 03:41:33.240
[Amit Varma]: and look at your book for the lucid explanation of this with the actual numbers where you say,

03:41:33.240 --> 03:41:37.640
[Amit Varma]: you don't need that much money to make money, right? You can start small, let it compound,

03:41:37.640 --> 03:41:42.280
[Amit Varma]: be disciplined, you know, let it earn value sleep and so on and so forth. And then you make a really

03:41:42.280 --> 03:41:46.520
[Amit Varma]: interesting point about the first crore, where you say, quote, the first crore you make will

03:41:46.520 --> 03:41:50.760
[Amit Varma]: largely come from your income from the work you do, your profession will pay you a salary or your

03:41:50.760 --> 03:41:54.760
[Amit Varma]: business will generate the cash, or you will join a startup which is acquired and voila, you have

03:41:54.760 --> 03:42:00.360
[Amit Varma]: some money, right? Which you know, is, again, many people won't kind of think in these terms,

03:42:00.360 --> 03:42:05.400
[Amit Varma]: everybody wants to, you know, get rich super fast and so on. And there is this old quip about

03:42:05.400 --> 03:42:11.400
[Amit Varma]: the easiest way to make a million dollars is to start with 10 million. So big and now you then,

03:42:11.400 --> 03:42:17.400
[Amit Varma]: you know, go into a bunch of sort of you give these bits of advice. And the first of those

03:42:17.400 --> 03:42:21.800
[Amit Varma]: is make money not returns. So, you know, explain this.

03:42:22.360 --> 03:42:26.440
[Guest]: This is actually okay, let me start with the first part. How much money do you need to make

03:42:26.440 --> 03:42:30.920
[Guest]: money is a question. And I told you about this, I said the difference between making the same

03:42:30.920 --> 03:42:37.080
[Guest]: amount of money with a high return mechanism, and the low return mechanism may be of the order of

03:42:37.080 --> 03:42:43.880
[Guest]: say 20 or 30,000 rupees per month. If you find it a little more comfortable to do the more risky one,

03:42:44.520 --> 03:42:49.640
[Guest]: sorry, the less risky one, then you just have to find out 20-30,000 rupees more. Now, the first

03:42:49.640 --> 03:42:55.160
[Guest]: crore that you make, and because you are, you know, you're going to be squeamish about investing

03:42:55.160 --> 03:42:58.760
[Guest]: most of your money, because it's hard earned money, you've just started to earn it and all

03:42:58.760 --> 03:43:04.440
[Guest]: that stuff. When you make your first crore, it will largely come from the income that you make,

03:43:04.440 --> 03:43:09.400
[Guest]: because your make, I'll give you just the simplest example, let's say you're starting off your salary

03:43:09.400 --> 03:43:15.720
[Guest]: career with about a 5 lakh per year salary. At this point, the amount you're saving is probably

03:43:15.720 --> 03:43:23.240
[Guest]: of the order of 30-40,000 rupees a year, I'm talking 3000 rupees a month. You work really hard,

03:43:23.240 --> 03:43:28.280
[Guest]: build yourself a YouTube course on SEO, I don't know whatever it is YouTube algorithm course,

03:43:28.280 --> 03:43:34.520
[Guest]: you get yourself an additional 5 lakh rupees. You made a 100% return on the time that you've

03:43:34.520 --> 03:43:42.440
[Guest]: invested from the 5 lakh to 10 lakh. This 10 lakh allows you to save from 50,000 to maybe 2 lakhs

03:43:42.440 --> 03:43:46.600
[Guest]: per year, your savings have gone up. But you know what, most of these returns have come because

03:43:46.600 --> 03:43:52.360
[Guest]: you've increased your income, not because your earnings from your, even if you'd invested those

03:43:52.360 --> 03:43:56.920
[Guest]: amount you had saved 50,000, do you think that would have ever resulted in a 5 lakh rupee per

03:43:56.920 --> 03:44:02.840
[Guest]: hour, 5 lakh rupee payout, chances are zero. Do the same thing, 10 lakhs becomes 20, 20 lakhs

03:44:02.840 --> 03:44:09.160
[Guest]: becomes 30. Your income can keep growing by the experience you gain, the courses you do,

03:44:09.160 --> 03:44:16.280
[Guest]: the skills you have, up to a certain point. So you start saving from there and slowly build up

03:44:16.280 --> 03:44:22.440
[Guest]: your corpus. After a few years you're earning 25-30 lakhs, maybe 10 years later, and you've

03:44:22.440 --> 03:44:27.640
[Guest]: got savings of about 50-60 lakhs. Most of these savings, if you look back about it,

03:44:27.640 --> 03:44:32.120
[Guest]: it will be coming in from the increased amounts of money you've been able to put in,

03:44:32.120 --> 03:44:37.240
[Guest]: largely because your income has increased. And when you get up to the first crore,

03:44:37.240 --> 03:44:41.800
[Guest]: you'll find that most of the money has started to come from that, the amount you've saved.

03:44:42.440 --> 03:44:48.920
[Guest]: It is beyond the one CR, is where your impact is more significant of the money you've saved,

03:44:48.920 --> 03:44:54.520
[Guest]: that overshadows the incremental income that you earn from your salary. Because at some point,

03:44:54.520 --> 03:44:58.200
[Guest]: we all stagnate in terms of salaries. Of course, in Bangalore, there's no such thing,

03:44:58.200 --> 03:45:01.640
[Guest]: but everywhere else, I think at some point, you kind of start getting to a point where you're

03:45:01.640 --> 03:45:10.280
[Guest]: getting the 5%, 10% increases, not the 50%, 60%. And because of that, the amount you're going to

03:45:10.280 --> 03:45:16.040
[Guest]: gain from the investments you make will start to look much better. So that's the early point of

03:45:16.040 --> 03:45:22.920
[Guest]: this. But if you focus your attention on growing your income in the early years, not what, where

03:45:22.920 --> 03:45:28.680
[Guest]: you save, you will get there in a much faster fashion, get there being, you have to figure out

03:45:28.680 --> 03:45:33.800
[Guest]: where you want to get to in the first place. But whatever that there is, you'll get there faster

03:45:33.800 --> 03:45:38.920
[Guest]: by just focusing on making more money from what you actually do, rather than earning money from

03:45:38.920 --> 03:45:44.520
[Guest]: your investments. That means I would say, take Amit Verma's clear writing course, it will have

03:45:44.520 --> 03:45:50.040
